name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: In the past year we have achieved an unprecedented rebound. We reopened our economy, kept our kids in school, and put families back to work! Help us continue that work for another four years to build a better tomorrow for the people of Rhode Island!    https://t.co/0z8XkJAMfQ  https://t.co/9acOlQHWjB

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: Thank you for the overwhelming support shown to our campaign last Thursday night. I am excited to continue working for hardworking families and small businesses. Together, we will continue the Rhode Island rebound, making our state an even better place to live!  https://t.co/OzQmhOYR7g

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: Municipal leaders in our 39 cities and towns have been key to our success in addressing the pandemic and getting our state back on track.   Local leaders will always have a seat at the table as we work together to move Rhode Island forward.  https://t.co/Kn6iqCKZhq

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: Proud to receive the support of @RI_Trades. They've been at the forefront in the fight for fair wages & economic security for working people—while also building a stronger RI for future generations. We'll continue our work together creating good jobs in all 39 cities & towns.  https://t.co/ipkfGQetcz

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: I'm honored to receive the support of the @LIUNA RI District Council. As essential workers during the pandemic, they have been key to RI leading the northeast in economic recovery. I look forward to continuing our work together to grow incomes and creating good paying jobs.  https://t.co/kZUYquvLyG

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: Over the last year, my focus has been on delivering an economic rebound for working people and Mayor Lombardi has been a key partner in our efforts. Thank you for your support and friendship, Mayor!  https://t.co/gw0yDA14pc

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: I'm grateful to have @MayorLBH's support in this election. She is a champion for hardworking families in Woonsocket and I look forward to continuing our work together to support Rhode Island's economic growth.  https://t.co/uOdqSyij8l

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: Mayor Polisena is a tireless advocate for hardworking people in his community and has been a key partner in our state's recovery efforts.  I'm grateful for his longtime friendship and his support for our campaign.  https://t.co/WBKiwPB66X

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: This past year, @Sabina_Matos has been an invaluable partner at Lt. Governor as we've worked together as a team to move Rhode Island forward.  We still have work to do for the state we love and I'm proud to have her support in my campaign for re-election.  https://t.co/Z78lh9URIY

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: I talked with @DomTurnerABC6 to reflect on my first year as Governor and the progress we've made as a state.  By coming together, we've accomplished a lot. Now, we're building on Rhode Island's momentum.  https://t.co/uVbwuCWvOd

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: We're building a campaign across Rhode Island's 39 cities and towns and need your help. You can join our campaign and make a contribution at ➡️  https://t.co/p4J9uugWhH

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: It's been an honor serving the people of Rhode Island this past year.  Together, we've reopened our economy responsibly and we're building a brighter future for this generation and the next⁠—across all of our 39 cities and towns.  We're just getting started.  https://t.co/xOjK5pPHBD

tweet: As Governor, I've worked closely with municipal leaders in our 39 cities and towns to ensure that we are building an economy that delivers for hardworking families. name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: It's important that we continue the Rhode Island rebound across all of our 39 cities and towns. That's why I announced yesterday that I'm running for re-election.  https://t.co/Hh99PCkadv

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: We have work to do – and we’re going to get it done. Because we will have a bright future in the next four years by working together.

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: In the year ahead, we’ll be cutting taxes for veterans, growing the jobs of the future, and investing in a once-in-a-generation effort to add affordable housing.

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: I’m running to create good jobs for those who need them, grow our economy in every corner of our state, and raise per capita income for everyone.
